  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN190.2-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">tōḻi cevilittāyk kaṟattoṭu niṉṟatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">How the confidante stood firm in duty to the foster mother.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN190.2">
      <lg type="edition">
        <l>tiraiyuḻan tacaiiya niraivaḷai yāyamō</l>
        <l>ṭuppiṉ kuppai yēṟi yeṟpaṭa</l>
        <l>varutimi leṇṇun tuṟaivaṉō ṭūrē</l>
        <l>yorutaṉ koṭumaiyi ṉalarpā ṭummē</l>
        <l>yalamaraṉ maḻaikka ṇamarntu nōkkā</l>
        <l>ṉalaiyal vāḻivēṇ ṭaṉṉai yuyarmicaip</l>
        <l>potumpiṟ puṉṉaic ciṉaiccēr pirunta</l>
        <l>vampa nārai yiriya vorunāṭ</l>
        <l>poṅkuvara lūtaiyoṭu puṇari yalaippa</l>
        <l>vuḻaikkaṭal vaḻaṅkalu muriya ṉataṉṟalai</l>
        <l>yiruṅkaḻip pukāar poruntat tākki</l>
        <l>vayaccuṟā veṟinteṉa valava ṉaḷippa</l>
        <l>veḻilpayaṅ kuṉṟiya ciṟaiyaḻi toḻila</l>
        <l>niraimaṇip puravi virainaṭai tavira</l>
        <l>viḻumeṉ kāṉal viḻumaṇa lacaii</l>
        <l>yāynta pariyaṉ vantivaṇ</l>
        <l>māṉṟa mālaic cērntaṉṟō vilaṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        <l>Because of the man from the ghat, (3c)</l>
        <l>where they, as night falls, alongside the girl companions with bangles in rows</l>
        <l>who had rested after bearing the waves, mount the heaps of salt (1f.)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">[and] count the boats that come, (3ab)</l>
        <l>the village, it sings with gossip, in its singular cruelty. (3df.)</l>
        <l>His look did not settle on [her with] fluttering rain eyes. (5)</l>
        <l>Don’t slap [her] oh mother, please. (6a-c)</l>
        <l>On top of his having the right of also roaming the nearby sea, (10)</l>
        <l>as the waves were rolling, with the cold wind coming with foam, (9)</l>
        <l>on one day, so that the new egrets retreated (8)</l>
        <l>that were perched close on the branches of the Puṉṉai trees in the grove</l>
        <l rend="indent8">of tall treetops, (6df.)</l>
        <l>as for [his] having come here, he with choice horses,</l>
        <l>joining [us] in gloomy evenings, he has not, (16f.)</l>
        <l>resting in the excellent sand of the rustling seashore grove, (15)</l>
        <l>while the horses with bells in rows were restrained in [their] fast gait, (14)</l>
        <l>straining against the confinement that diminished the amount of [their] grace, (13)</l>
        <l>while the charioteer comforts [them], because sharp sharks were dashing [at them], (12)</l>
        <l>attacking, as is fitting [for them], those who do not enter the dark backwaters of vast area. (10df.)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
